<h2>Check your qualifications</h2>
<p>To train to teach in primary and secondary schools in England, you’ll need:</p>
<ul>
<li>GCSEs at grade 4 (C) or above in English and maths (and science if you want to teach primary) </li>
<li>a bachelor’s degree in any subject </li>
</ul>
<p>Modern languages teacher training courses have had successful applications from candidates with a range of degrees, including international relations, psychology, sociology and journalism.</p>
<p><a href="/non-uk-teachers/train-to-teach-in-england-as-an-international-student">Non-UK citizens can find out more about training to teach in England</a>.</p>
<p>If your training provider thinks you need to top up your languages knowledge, you might need to do <a href="/how-to-apply-for-teacher-training/subject-knowledge-enhancement">subject knowledge enhancement (SKE)</a> before you start your teacher training.</p>
<p><a href="/is-teaching-right-for-me/qualifications-you-need-to-teach">Find out more about the qualifications needed to train to teach</a>.</p>
<h2> Fund your teacher training </h2>
<p>Tax-free bursaries of £25,000 are available for all eligible trainee language teachers.</p>
<p>Tax-free scholarships of £27,000 are available for eligible trainee French, German, and Spanish languages teachers.</p>
<a href="/funding-and-support/scholarships-and-bursaries">Find out more about bursaries and scholarships</a>.</p>
  <p>You can receive this alongside a tuition fee and a maintenance loan. </p>

  <p>You may also be able to get <a href="/funding-and-support">extra funding support</a> if you're: </p>
  <ul>
<li>a parent or carer </li>
<li>disabled </li>
</ul>
<p>Non-UK citizens are eligible for bursaries and scholarships for modern languages teacher training courses. </p>
<p>You can <a href="/non-uk-teachers/fees-and-funding-for-non-uk-trainees">find out more about fees and financial support available for non-UK citizens</a>.</p>

    <h2>Paid internship </h2>

<p>If you’re currently doing an undergraduate or master's degree and are interested in teaching modern languages, you could apply for a <a href="/is-teaching-right-for-me/teaching-internship-providers">paid teaching internship</a>. </p>

<p>The 3-week programme could help you to understand what it’s really like in the classroom and get a feel for school life. </p>

